/</a></p></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci gj no np nq\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt\"></span></div><div class=\"gn go gp gq gr\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq or os bl\" id=\"26a9\">Table of Contents</h2><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"015a\"><em class=\"mt\">Project Introduction</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"8767\"><em class=\"mt\">Assumptions</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"19b8\"><em class=\"mt\">Technical Overview</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"2ed6\"><em class=\"mt\">Data Collection and Validation</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"f1aa\"><em class=\"mt\">Statistical Analysis</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"7443\"><em class=\"mt\">Visualizations and Results</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"2836\"><em class=\"mt\">Key Findings</em></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4d8c\"><em class=\"mt\">Conclusion</em></li></ul></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci gj no np nq\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt\"></span></div><div class=\"gn go gp gq gr\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq or os bl\" id=\"3143\">Introduction</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"0732\">Since 2022, Large Language Models (LLMs) and Generative AI have been increasingly integrated into traditional software, making understanding their capabilities and limitations crucial. While these models are designed to generate human-like text responses, an intriguing question arises: <strong class=\"lx gv\">Can they produce truly random numbers when asked?</strong> Randomness is a fundamental aspect of fields like simulations, gaming, cryptography, and statistics. True randomness implies that every possible number within a specified range has an equal probability of being chosen. This project explores whether AI language models, such as <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">GPT-4</code>, exhibit true randomness in number generation when prompted.</p><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"3d7d\">Assumptions</h2><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"1956\">Randomness in LLMs</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"f46f\">The concept of randomness in LLMs presents an interesting paradox. LLMs are fundamentally non-random systems trained to predict the most probable next token based on their training data and context. This core mechanism inherently conflicts with true randomness, as the models are designed to find and replicate patterns rather than generate random outputs.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"f22f\">The training process of LLMs involves minimizing prediction errors and maximizing the likelihood of \u201ccorrect\u201d responses based on their training data. When asked to generate a random number, an LLM might:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"2a0f\">Draw from patterns it has observed in its training data</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"59bd\">Attempt to mimic what it perceives as \u201crandom\u201d behavior</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"147f\">Use internal numerical representations that may introduce unintended biases</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"576a\">This fundamental architecture makes true randomness particularly challenging for LLMs, as they are essentially pattern-matching engines rather than something that possesses the ability to simulate randomness.</p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"39c7\">Pseudo-Randomness</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"88f1\">It\u2019s important to note that even traditional computing systems don\u2019t generate <em class=\"mt\">truly</em> random numbers. Instead, they use Pseudo-Random Number Generators (PRNGs) that create sequences of numbers that appear to be random but are actually deterministic based on an initial seed value.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"a777\">Popular packages like Python\u2019s <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">NumPy</code> use different algorithms to generate pseudo-random numbers.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"e5d6\">These PRNGs work by:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"43cd\">1. Starting with a seed value (often derived from system time or hardware events)</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"6781\">2. Applying mathematical transformations to generate subsequent numbers</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"6b62\">3. Producing sequences that pass statistical tests for randomness</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"f698\">While not truly random, these methods are well-studied and provide sufficient randomness for most applications.</p><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"0671\">Technical Overview</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"803f\">The project consists of several key components:</p><ol class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms qg oz pa bl\" id=\"0628\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Data Collection and Validation</strong>: Gathering numbers generated by various AI language models and traditional random number generators within specified ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms qg oz pa bl\" id=\"63e3\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Data Processing</strong>: Normalizing the responses and preparing the data for statistical analysis.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms qg oz pa bl\" id=\"bd0c\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Statistical Analysis</strong>: Evaluating the distributions of the generated numbers to assess randomness.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms qg oz pa bl\" id=\"2dbd\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Visualizations and Results</strong>: Creating visual representations to compare the randomness of AI models against traditional methods.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms qg oz pa bl\" id=\"634b\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Key Findings</strong>: Summarizing the insights gained from the analysis.</li></ol><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"a462\">Data Collection and Validation</h2><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"eb9c\">AI Language Models Used</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"1e19\">To assess the randomness of AI language models, I tested several versions of OpenAI\u2019s <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\"><a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://platform.openai.com/docs/models\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">GPT-4</a></code><a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://platform.openai.com/docs/models\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"> model family</a>, and various popular open-source models by Meta and Google.</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"0688\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">chatgpt-4o-latest</code> (tested date: 2024\u201311\u201302)</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"c093\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4\u20130613</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"a3b3\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024\u201308\u201306</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"5060\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024\u201307\u201318</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"235d\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\"><a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://huggingface.co/lmstudio-community/gemma-2-9b-it-GGUF\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gemma-2-9B-it</a></code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"761b\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\"><a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://huggingface.co/lmstudio-community/gemma-2-2b-it-GGUF\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gemma-2-2B-it</a></code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"809f\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\"><a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://huggingface.co/mlx-community/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-4bit\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">llama-3.2-3B-instruct</a></code></li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"cdd3\">These models were prompted to generate a random number between X and Y, where X and Y define the range. The ranges varied widely to test the models across different scales, including positive, negative, and mixed ranges.</p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"848d\">Traditional Random Number Generators</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"1964\">To provide a baseline for comparison, I also collected numbers using:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"712f\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Python\u2019s built-in </strong><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code><strong class=\"lx gv\"> module</strong> (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random.uniform(range_min, range_max)</code>)</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"ecf7\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">NumPy</code><strong class=\"lx gv\">\u2019s random generator</strong> (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy.random.uniform(range_min, range_max)</code>)</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"f005\">These generators are widely accepted for producing uniformly distributed random numbers and serve as control methods for the analysis.</p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"ce9a\">Data Collection Process</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"9fb3\">For each model and method, I generated one random number within each specified range, 200 times<strong class=\"lx gv\"> </strong>(therefore, <strong class=\"lx gv\">n=200</strong> for each of these experiment subsets):</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"eb6e\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Ranges Used</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"acd7\">0 to 10</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"f265\">0 to 100</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4fe1\">-745 to -556</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"2f6e\">-359 to 39</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"3bea\">328 to 508</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"f7e9\">-647 to 489</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"41a6\">-863 to 557</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"3c4e\">The use of diverse ranges, including small and large intervals as well as positive, negative, and mixed ranges, aims to help identify any potential biases or limitations in the AI models\u2019 number generation capabilities. This variety allows us to test whether the models perform consistently across different numerical contexts and whether certain types of ranges (e.g., negative numbers or larger intervals) pose particular challenges for AI-generated randomness.</p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"63c0\">Data Validation</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"a124\">Responses from the AI models were validated to ensure they fell within the specified ranges. Any invalid responses were excluded from the analysis.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"1f97\">There was only models that generated invalid value (outside of the provided range): <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024\u201308\u201306</code>, with range <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-359, 39]</code>, generating the value <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">\u2013361</code>, and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">llama-3.2-3B-instruct</code>, with its invalid response counts distributed as follows:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"fdda\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-359, 39]</code>: 149</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"cb4b\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-863, 557]</code>: 127</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"81b6\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-647, 489]</code>: 84</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"ad2a\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[328, 508]</code>: 4</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"3a17\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-745, -556]</code>: 3</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"cac4\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 10]</code>: 3</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"d397\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 100]</code>: 1</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"d8ee\">Statistical Analysis</h2><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"f412\">Normalization of Responses</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"29ef\">To enable a fair comparison across different ranges, I normalized all responses using the following formula:</p><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc mu mv paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qh\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 1400w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*E5i3VaU96CDWJSp78INnPQ.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"61\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author \u2014 Min-max number response normalization function</figcaption></figure><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"4815\">This scaling operation transforms all numbers to a 0 to 1 scale, where 0 represents the minimum of the range and 1 represents the maximum.</p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"11e2\">Range Size Calculation</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"8ec7\">The size of each range is calculated as:</p><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc mu mv paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qi\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 1400w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*EDJXqvr94ftOYY7cWUKojg.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"42\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author \u2014 Range Size Calculation</figcaption></figure><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"44cd\">This information was used to analyze how the range size might affect the randomness of the AI models\u2019 outputs.</p><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"1edb\">Visualizations and Results</h2><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"a2ac\">Distribution of Random Values by Range</h3><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"8e7d\">To visualize the distribution of normalized responses, I created a density plot comparing the AI models to the traditional random generators.</p></div></div><div class=\"nc\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"la qj lb qk lc ql cm qm cn qn cp bi\"><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc qp qq paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qo\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/format:webp/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 2000w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/1*kJ9QvKTFzmA-7UfU-7Pjuw.png 2000w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"500\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"1000\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"3e25\"><em class=\"mt\">This image is a </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">density plot</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> that compares the distribution of </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">normalized responses</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> generated by all tested </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">generation methods</em></strong><em class=\"mt\">. Each curve represents the density (or relative frequency) of normalized values produced by a specific method, allowing us to see if any method shows biases toward certain normalized values.</em></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"40b4\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">X-Axis (Normalized Response)</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"7bcc\">Represents the normalized response, ranging from approximately 0\u20131.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"2994\">A value of 0 corresponds to the minimum of the range, and 1 corresponds to the maximum.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"9054\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Y-Axis (Density)</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"070b\">Represents the relative frequency with which each normalized response value occurs for each method.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"946b\">Higher peaks indicate a higher frequency of certain values.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"db6a\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Legend:</strong></p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"6ebc\">Blue: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">chatgpt-4o-latest</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4d9f\">Pink: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4c60\">Black: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"5d8f\">Orange: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4-0613</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"208f\">Green: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024-08-06</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"33b5\">Purple: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"1747\">Gray: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">llama-3.2-3b-instruct</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"8a64\">Red: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">python-numpy</code></li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"e8f1\">Brown: <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">python-random</code></li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"fc79\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Observations:</strong></p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4671\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Traditional Random Generators </strong>(<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>): Both produce balanced distributions centered around 0.5, indicative of uniform randomness.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"da82\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">AI Models:</strong></p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"0dff\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code> exhibit notable peaks at specific normalized values, suggesting biases.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"9da1\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> shows sharp peaks around 0.3 and 0.7, indicating a tendency toward lower and higher normalized values.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"5efd\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">llama-3.2-3b-instruct</code> has a pronounced peak near 0.9, suggesting a skew towards higher values.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"fb31\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">chatgpt-4o-latest</code>, <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4-0613</code>, and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024-08-06</code> display smoother curves with slight peaks near 0.5, but they are not uniformly distributed, indicating minor pattern-based biases.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"e619\">Mean Normalized Response vs. Range Size</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"e1d0\">To assess how the range size affects the randomness of the outputs, I plotted the mean normalized response against the range size for each generation method.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"9c1f\">The range size is the distance between the minimum boundary and the maximum boundary of each given range. For example, the range size for the range [0, 10] = 10.</p></div></div><div class=\"nc\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"la qj lb qk lc ql cm qm cn qn cp bi\"><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc qp qq paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qr\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/format:webp/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 2000w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/1*Rlq3xEEDxG7nNxyfYXUc-Q.png 2000w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"433\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"1000\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"489d\"><em class=\"mt\">This image is a </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">line chart</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> that shows the relationship between </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">mean normalized response</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> and </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">range size</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> for various </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">generation methods</em></strong><em class=\"mt\">. Each line represents a different method, allowing for comparison of how each method\u2019s mean normalized response changes as the range size increases.</em></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"ebc2\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">X-Axis (Range Size)</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"06d3\">Represents the size of the range, from 0 to approximately 1400.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"270e\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Y-Axis (Mean Normalized Response)</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"76ce\">Shows the average normalized value generated by each method, ranging from 0.30 to 0.65.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"6bee\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Observations:</strong></p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"596f\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Traditional Random Generators</strong> (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>): Both maintain a stable mean around 0.5 across all range sizes, reflecting uniform randomness.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"01b9\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code>: Shows a marked downward trend as the range size increases, suggesting a bias towards generating lower normalized values in larger ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"c633\">Slight fluctuations are present, but most models hover near the midpoint, indicating closer adherence to uniform distribution than <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code>.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"b37c\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code>: Display initial peaks in smaller ranges, suggesting possible tendencies toward specific values in constrained ranges before stabilizing in larger ranges.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"baa3\">Distribution of Prime Numbers</h2></div></div><div class=\"nc\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"la qj lb qk lc ql cm qm cn qn cp bi\"><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc qp qq paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qs\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/format:webp/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 2000w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/1*fmNf1R9Oo1IyuoBTY1hwzA.png 2000w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"567\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"1000\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"ccba\"><em class=\"mt\">This visualization compares how frequently each method generates </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">prime numbers</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> against the </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">expected probability</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> of a prime number being generated within each range. A </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">ratio of 1.0</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> indicates </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">perfect alignment</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> with </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">theoretical probabilities</em></strong><em class=\"mt\">, while higher or lower values suggest </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">over or under-representation </em></strong><em class=\"mt\">of prime numbers, respectively.</em></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"981f\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Observations:</strong></p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"c256\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Traditional Random Generators </strong>(<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>): Both generally maintain ratios close to 1.0 across larger ranges, aligning well with expected prime distributions.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"be70\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">AI Models:</strong> Significant deviations from expected probabilities are evident:</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"408c\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> shows extreme deviations, notably with a ratio of 3.11 in the <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 10]</code> range and 2.67 in <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-359, 39]</code>, suggesting a strong over-representation of primes.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"0563\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code> also exhibit elevated ratios, especially in smaller ranges, with values exceeding 2.5 in certain intervals.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"71f4\">Newer models (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024-08-06</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">chatgpt-4o-latest</code>) show moderate over-representation, with ratios slightly above 1.0 across most ranges.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"b628\">Distribution of Round Numbers (Ending in 5 or 0)</h2></div></div><div class=\"nc\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"la qj lb qk lc ql cm qm cn qn cp bi\"><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc qp qq paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qs\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/format:webp/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 2000w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/1*X9lGLuVFCD_vFEulOvl68A.png 2000w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"567\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"1000\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"17dd\"><em class=\"mt\">This visualization compares the </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">empirical probability</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> of generating numbers </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">ending in 5 or 0</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> against their </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">expected frequency</em></strong><em class=\"mt\">. A </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">ratio of 1.0</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> indicates </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">perfect alignment</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> with theoretical probabilities, while values </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">below or above 1.0</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> suggest </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">under or over-representation</em></strong><em class=\"mt\">, respectively.</em></p><h3 class=\"pp nw gu bg nx pq pr ps ob pt pu pv of mg pw px py mk pz qa qb mo qc qd qe qf bl\" id=\"3b64\"><strong class=\"an\">Observations:</strong></h3><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"a280\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Traditional Random Generators </strong>(<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>): Both maintain ratios close to 1.0 across most ranges, indicating they generate numbers ending in 5 or 0 at expected frequencies.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"bc28\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> consistently underrepresents numbers ending in 5 or 0 across all ranges, with notably low ratios, especially in the <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 10]</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 100]</code> ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"1422\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code> display significant deviations, with extremely high ratios (e.g., 1.90 in <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[-647, 489]</code> and 1.13 in <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 10]</code> for <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code>), indicating an over-representation in certain ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"d1e6\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Range Influence</strong>: Smaller ranges (e.g., <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 10]</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">[0, 100]</code>) exhibit more pronounced deviations from expected probabilities, suggesting that the distribution of ending digits is impacted by range size.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"85c2\">Boxplot of Normalized Responses Across Ranges</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"9b11\">To further examine the distribution of responses, I created boxplots of the normalized responses for each generation method across different ranges.</p></div></div><div class=\"nc\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"la qj lb qk lc ql cm qm cn qn cp bi\"><figure class=\"mx my mz na nb nc qp qq paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nd ne eo nf bi ng\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mu mv qt\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/format:webp/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 2000w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 1000px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:2000/1*vPTk7Z9TJRoWxHMfUa6LrQ.png 2000w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lf nh c\" height=\"538\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"1000\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"ni nj nk mu mv nl nm bg b bh ab ee\">Image by author</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"c691\"><em class=\"mt\">This image is a </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">boxplot visualization</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> that compares the </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">normalized response distributions</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> of various </em><strong class=\"lx gv\"><em class=\"mt\">generation methods</em></strong><em class=\"mt\"> across different number ranges. The plot allows us to see how the responses of different models and methods are distributed within specified ranges after normalizing the values.</em></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"5326\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Boxplot Elements</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"5e3b\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Boxes</strong>: Each plot <strong class=\"lx gv\">box</strong><em class=\"mt\"> </em>represents the interquartile range (IQR), containing the middle 50% of the data.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"a26d\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Median Line</strong>: Marks the median (50th percentile) of the responses.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"109b\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Whiskers</strong>: Extend to show the range within 1.5 times the IQR.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"5dbe\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Outliers</strong>: Dots outside the whiskers indicating values outside the typical spread.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"998a\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Observations</strong>:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"942e\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Traditional Random Generators</strong> (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>): Both exhibit consistent medians near 0.5 with wide interquartile ranges (IQRs), indicating balanced distributions across ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4f6f\">Show varied spreads and central tendencies. For instance, some models have narrower IQRs or medians that deviate from 0.5, revealing non-uniform distributions.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"d102\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> often has lower medians and tighter IQRs, indicating a tendency to generate values clustered toward the lower end, especially in larger ranges.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"b389\">Other models, such as <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4-0613</code>, exhibit slightly shifted medians or wider spreads, suggesting mild biases in value distribution.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"2a34\">Key Findings</h2><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"c50b\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">AI Models vs. Traditional Random Generators:</strong> Traditional random generators (<code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">numpy</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">random</code>) demonstrate consistent performance across all ranges, producing values that align well with uniform randomness. In contrast, AI models display significant deviations, with biases that differ across models and ranges.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"234b\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Biases in AI Models:</strong> Specific AI models, such as <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> and the <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma</code> family models, show pronounced biases. For example:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"cd8e\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> tends to underrepresent certain values, with lower medians and narrower distributions, especially in larger ranges. This model also consistently underrepresents numbers ending in 5 or 0.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"7318\"><code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-9b-it</code> frequently over-represent prime numbers and show an unusually high probability for numbers ending in 5 or 0, especially in smaller ranges.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"b3c5\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Impact of Range Size:</strong> Range size plays a crucial role in shaping AI model responses:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"8fc3\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Smaller ranges</strong> tend to amplify certain biases, such as over-representation of primes in models like <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gemma-2-2b-it</code>.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"02c5\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Larger ranges</strong> exacerbate the downward trend in mean normalized responses for models like <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18</code>, highlighting a systematic skew toward lower values.</li></ul><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"5695\"><strong class=\"lx gv\">Response Distribution Consistency:</strong> AI models lack uniformity in their value distributions compared to traditional generators:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"4438\">While some models like <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">chatgpt-4o-latest</code> and <code class=\"de pg ph pi pj b\">gpt-4o-2024-08-06</code> approach uniformity with smoother distributions, others exhibit distinct peaks and biases.</li><li class=\"lv lw gu lx b ly pb ma mb mc pc me mf mg pd mi mj mk pe mm mn mo pf mq mr ms oy oz pa bl\" id=\"d8d3\">The variability across models suggests that AI-generated randomness is highly model-dependent, with different architectures and training data likely influencing response tendencies.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nv nw gu bg nx ny pk oa ob oc pl oe of og pm oi oj ok pn om on oo po oq or os bl\" id=\"b142\">Conclusion</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly ot ma mb mc ou me mf mg ov mi mj mk ow mm mn mo ox mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"7419\">While AI language models are adept at generating human-like text, their ability to produce truly random numbers is limited. The deviations from uniform randomness observed in the AI models suggest inherent biases, possibly stemming from their training data or inherent patterns in language generation.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"31e4\">For applications requiring true randomness, relying solely on AI language models may not be sufficient. Traditional random number generators remain the reliable choice for such needs.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"c58f\">Understanding these limitations is crucial, especially as AI models become more integrated into systems where randomness plays a critical role.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"b013\">Thank you for reading! For more details or to contribute, please visit the project repository.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"ac ci gj no np nq\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt nu\"></span><span class=\"nr by bn ns nt\"></span></div><div class=\"gn go gp gq gr\"><div class=\"ac ci\"><div class=\"cp bi fv fw fx fy\"><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"dfee\">Project GitHub Repository: <a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://github.com/kmaurinjones/llm-randomness-analysis\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/kmaurinjones/llm-randomness-analysis</a></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lv lw gu lx b ly lz ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms gn bl\" id=\"11cc\">LinkedIn: <a class=\"ah nn\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/</a></p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article>"}
